                    <h1 class="domdom">10</h1>

                    <h1>Film: <a href="/on/film/613">Orphee (1950)</a></h1>

                    <h2>10 Jun 2010, 7:30 p.m.</h2>

                    <p>Poet, playwright, artist and filmmaker, Jean Cocteau was one of the most significant artists of the 20th century, and Orphee is one of his finest films. This magical retelling of the Orpheus myth turns the singer of Greek legend, into a famous left-bank poet in post-war Paris. With famous mirror dissolving and flying tricks, this is hauntingly beautiful.</p>

                    <p class="viewlink"><a href="/on/film/613">Read More &raquo;</a></p>

